  "title": "Public Relations Officer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Handle enquiries and feedback relating to the projects as well as follow-up on actions to resolve it</li>\n  <li>Maintain good and positive relation with the residents.</li>\n  <li>To serve as a liaison for all public relations matter for the new contract</li>\n  <li>To assist the Authority in the running of their PR programmes</li>\n  <li>Attend meetings, briefings, presentations with Authority</li>\n  <li>Documentation, monitor and tabulate report from public feedback</li>\n  <li>Meeting with an entity for areas of improvement</li>\n  <li>Other ad-hoc duties with regards to Customer service</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum qualification of GCE \"O\" Level Certificate, with public relations work experience preferred.</li>\n  <li>Min of 3 years of experience in Construction field</li>\n  <li>Competent and possesses the skill, knowledge, and ability to manage public relation issues and general project queries with the residents effectively.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, able to communicate with staff of all levels in the company.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge in Microsoft Office programs</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and diligently, prioritize tasks assigned.</li>\n  <li>Able to speak fluent English and one other official language.</li>\n</ul>",
